<TITLE> Welcome rains jeopardise public mobility </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 5 (bdnews24.com) Influenced by a western low, Dhaka skies have been pouring welcome showers almost incessantly since early morning Tuesday, breaking the spell of sweltering heat. The sun was not visible to the Dhakaites till 1 pm. The rains made it extremely difficult for commuters making it to their work places though. Most city roads didn't see any traffic policemen and so even the limited mobile traffic soon became stagnant on many of the waterlogged lanes, roads and avenues. The weather office said different regions in the country experienced the rainfall after a prolonged and persistent heat wave. Weather expert Ayesha Khatun told bdnews24.com moderate to drizzling rains are expected to continue through the day. Dhaka rainfall during the last 24 hours registered a 61 mm mark. The highest and the lowest temperatures in the recorded Monday were 35.5 degrees C and 20.8 degress C. The highest and the lowest temperatures in Dhaka were 32.8 degrees C and 22.5 degrees C. bdnews24.com/ 
